{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"easeOut","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"duration","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TimeInterval","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@NSTimeInterval"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Animation","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animation","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore9AnimationV"}]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The length of time, expressed in seconds, that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the animation takes to complete.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"duration"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"return-value","level":2,"text":"Return Value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An ease-out animation with a specified duration.","type":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"An easing animation provides motion with a natural feel by varying","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the acceleration and deceleration of the animation, which matches","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"how things tend to move in reality. With an ease out animation, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"motion starts quickly and decreases its speed towards the end.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"easeOut(duration:)"},{"type":"text","text":" when you want to specify the time it takes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the animation to complete. Otherwise, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animation\/easeOut"},{"type":"text","text":" to perform"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the animation for a default length of time."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The following code shows an example of animating the size changes of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Circle","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" using an ease out animation with a duration of one","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"second.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct ContentView: View {","    @State private var scale = 0.5","","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            Circle()","                .scale(scale)","                .animation(.easeOut(duration: 1.0), value: scale)","            HStack {","                Button(\"+\") { scale += 0.1 }","                Button(\"-\") { scale -= 0.1 }","            }","        }","    }","}"]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/animation\/easeout(duration:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animation\/easeOut(duration:)"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animation"]]},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore9AnimationV7easeOut8durationACSd_tFZ","title":"easeOut(duration:)","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"easeOut","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"duration","kind":"externalParam"},{"